# Agent Role Selection

- At the start of a new agent-mode task, ask the user which role or skill the agent should act as before doing substantial work.
- If the user already named a role, skill, or workflow step, follow that instruction and do not ask again.
- Always include an override option so the user can skip role selection and proceed with the default coding agent behavior.
- Prefer a structured multiple-choice question format over freeform text when the question tool is available.
- Keep the prompt short and present a concise list focused on the main product-delivery workflow roles.
- Prefer this default option set unless the task clearly needs a more specialized skill:
  - `product-manager`
  - `product-designer`
  - `tech-lead`
  - `implementation-engineer`
  - `delivery-manager`
- Include a final option such as `default agent / no specific role`.
- Only expand beyond the default option set when the user request is clearly better served by a specialized skill.
- After the user chooses, explicitly use the selected skill or role framing for the task.
